## Context

Ticket 0115 delivered C2ST analytical null overlay (PR #769).  This ticket
covers the L1 JS-divergence analytical null, which requires vocabulary size
and document counts (no embeddings).

## Formula

E[JS | H₀] ≈ (V − 1) / 4 × (1/n_before + 1/n_after)   (Archer et al. 2014)
null_std = O(1/n) — see Archer et al. for the full variance expression.

V = vocabulary size (number of features after TF-IDF vectorisation),
n_before/n_after = document counts in each window.

## Actions

1. Extend `compute_analytical_null.py` to accept `--method L1`.
2. Add L1 branch to `_iter_window_counts` using `load_lexical_data(None)`
   and the L1 TF-IDF vocabulary size.
3. Add `tab_analytical_null_L1.csv` Make target in `zoo.mk`.
4. Pass `--analytical-null` to zoo figure recipe for L1.

## Test

Red: assert `l1_analytical_null(V=100, n_b=200, n_a=200)` returns
null_mean ≈ (99/4)*(1/200 + 1/200) within 1%.

## Depends on

- PR #769 (ticket 0115, C2ST analytical null infrastructure) — merged

## Exit criteria

- L1 analytical null implemented and schema-validated
- Zoo figure for L1 shows overlapping MC + analytical ribbons
- Tests pass; PR merged
